SIMPLE: watchword
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Watchword
<hw>Watch"word`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A word
given to sentinels, and to such as have occasion to visit the guards,
used as a signal by which a friend is known from an enemy, or a person
who has a right to pass the watch from one who has not; a countersign; a
password.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sentiment or motto; esp., one used as a rallying
cry or a signal for action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor deal in <qex>watchwords</qex> overmuch.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water</ent>⟦br⟧
